123
00:11:43,443 --> 00:11:47,866
Good afternoon, Director Schrader and members of the Cannabis Advisory Committee.

124
00:11:48,266 --> 00:11:51,288
My name is Brian Keith, one of the principals at En Route Home Delivery.

125
00:11:51,868 --> 00:11:55,491
I'm joined today by my fellow founders, Joanne, Rokia, and Solomon.

126
00:11:56,412 --> 00:12:05,316
Today, we will be discussing our proposal for a cannabis delivery operator license for en route home delivery to be cited at 151 Mystic Ave in Medford, Mass.

127
00:12:08,117 --> 00:12:11,998
Our mission statement speaks to who we are and is a true expression of our values.

128
00:12:12,599 --> 00:12:23,503
En route's mission is to build a community conscious adult use cannabis business that engages, serves and benefits communities of color and other disadvantaged communities through financial success and social responsibility.

129
00:12:24,194 --> 00:12:28,536
En Route Home Delivery Medford is 100% minority owned and majority women owned.

130
00:12:29,116 --> 00:12:40,561
Our team members are the, our team are members of the City of Boston Equity Program, as well as the State of Massachusetts Social Equity Program administered by the Cannabis Control Commission.

131
00:12:44,203 --> 00:12:51,686
We are excited about our proposal in Medford because when we join a community, we truly become active members of the community.

132
00:12:52,845 --> 00:13:03,411
Joanne is a chair of the Ward 8 Democratic Committee in Boston, member of the Massport CAC, and a member of a Patient and Family Advisory Committee for a local NICU.

133
00:13:04,151 --> 00:13:07,473
Rokia is a member of Roslindale Main Streets in Boston.

134
00:13:08,133 --> 00:13:13,656
Solomon is a member of the Central Square Business Association, as well as Roxbury Main Streets Organization.

135
00:13:14,237 --> 00:13:20,380
I hold a position of chair of the board of trustees for a local charter school.

136
00:13:20,978 --> 00:13:32,144
a member of the Roxbury Main Streets Board as well, a member of the UUUM Board in Roxbury, and until recently, I handled aircraft logistics for a Massachusetts-based private jet company.

137
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:40,089
Salman and Rokia Chowdhury are a husband and wife team with more than 22 years of local business and ownership experience.

138
00:13:40,609 --> 00:13:50,735
Their portfolio includes Shanti, three full-service Indian restaurants in Dorchester, Roslindale, and Kendall Square, the Dudley Cafe, a coffee shop in Roxbury's Newbeen Square,

139
00:13:51,306 --> 00:13:54,827
and 250 plus real estate developments and investments.

140
00:13:55,367 --> 00:14:02,210
Shanti Express, a fourth Indian restaurant, is a delivery-only kitchen concept, not dissimilar from our proposal this evening.

141
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:20,576
Together, we have 20 years as small business owners, 30 years as community advocates, 16 years in fleet logistics, expertise in areas of retail operations, luxury marketing, and regulated industries, and five plus years of planning and research in local cannabis space

142
00:14:21,343 --> 00:14:25,887
And we're in the final stages of opening a cannabis retail establishment at 331 Newberry Street.

143
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:46,086
We have had the pleasure of working through both the City of Boston licensing and permitting and zoning process for our adult use cannabis establishment approved on Newberry Street.

144
00:14:46,607 --> 00:14:51,951
We are nearly complete with the CCC process at this location and are awaiting approval of our final license.

145
00:14:52,451 --> 00:15:04,940
You will see on this slide before and after images of the initial state of our facility, truly creating a cannabis boutique in the retail heart of the City of Boston.

146
00:15:05,395 --> 00:15:12,577
And to be clear, the bottom images are the images of the before and the after are the top images, not the other way around.

147
00:15:15,477 --> 00:15:21,359
These next images display our family-friendly participation in Open Newberry over the past six Sundays.

148
00:15:22,359 --> 00:15:27,880
Open Newberry is an event where the entirety of Newberry Street is closed to vehicular traffic and becomes a pedestrian way.

149
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:34,022
This past Sunday, we invited Girl Paul Creamery, a Black-owned ice cream shop from Boston's Dorchester neighborhood,

150
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,934
to hand out complimentary ice cream to passersby.

151
00:15:36,954 --> 00:15:45,337
We are excited to, of course, compensate Grifoil Creamery for their work, but also give them the exposure to the foot traffic and disposable income found on Newbury Street.

152
00:15:45,997 --> 00:15:48,718
Uplifting small businesses is integral to everything we do.

153
00:15:57,673 --> 00:16:05,020
A delivery operator is a business that receives wholesale cannabis from licensed marijuana cultivators and marijuana product manufacturers.

154
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:17,751
The wholesale product is stored in a secure vault at 151 Mystic Avenue until it's securely transferred from the vault to one of En-Route's three secure all-electric vehicles for delivery to customers.

155
00:16:20,235 --> 00:16:25,336
Here, you'll be able to see a sketch of our proposed interior layout.

156
00:16:26,256 --> 00:16:35,378
This shows very small on our screen, so after the presentation, if there is interest, we can revisit this slide and make it bigger.

157
00:16:36,298 --> 00:16:45,239
Regarding delivery, En Route delivers to customers who are 21 years of age or older at their home residence or to licensed marijuana operators.

158
00:16:45,739 --> 00:16:49,940
Deliveries to dorms, government housing, hotels, or similar are strictly prohibited.

159
00:16:50,438 --> 00:16:59,746
To ensure that all requirements for delivery are met, prior to placing an order for delivery, all customers are required to pre-register and submit proof of age and residence verification.

160
00:17:00,247 --> 00:17:02,849
Age is verified again on camera at time of delivery.

161
00:17:03,309 --> 00:17:09,975
All delivery vehicles will be staffed with at least two employees, and during delivery, the vehicles will not be left alone at any time.

162
00:17:11,677 --> 00:17:15,060
It is important to note that there is absolutely no public component to this operation.

163
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:21,336
There will be no registers on site nor will there be any customers or members of the public coming into the facility at any time.

164
00:17:22,797 --> 00:17:25,919
Our last delivery must be in the customer's hands by 9 p.m.

165
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,541
or it will be delivered the following day.

166
00:17:29,322 --> 00:17:31,283
We will be a fully self-contained site.

167
00:17:31,903 --> 00:17:37,267
As a transportation business, we'll be looking closely at how best to optimize delivery schedules around peak commuter times.

168
00:17:37,847 --> 00:17:41,930
There will be no delivery vehicles allowed to park alongside the street.

169
00:17:42,572 --> 00:17:49,978
and we will be employing GPS technology to track all vehicles, ensuring vans safe entry into and out of the facility.

170
00:17:50,999 --> 00:17:57,124
Centrally located, EnRoute will have the ability to deliver with speed across the city of Medford and to surrounding communities.

171
00:17:57,764 --> 00:18:01,047
Our hours of operations, as you can see, are 10 a.m.

172
00:18:01,527 --> 00:18:02,128
to 9 p.m.

173
00:18:02,148 --> 00:18:05,831
Apologies for the dog.

174
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:28,224
40 state certified employees, including 12 delivery drivers and 28 warehouse staff, dispatch, security, with a preference to local BIPOC and veteran and LGBTQ individuals.

175
00:18:29,165 --> 00:18:34,006
We plan on creating 40 jobs at En Route Medford with a preference for Medford residents.

176
00:18:34,286 --> 00:18:39,087
Our hope is that we are hiring in such a local manner that our employees will have the opportunity to walk to work.

177
00:18:39,637 --> 00:18:46,840
We estimate a payroll budget that will see employees averaging a salary of $75,000, well above what is considered a living wage.

178
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:52,222
Employees will have access to full medical, dental, and vision benefits, including 401k.

179
00:18:53,263 --> 00:18:59,425
Additionally, we have created a profit sharing program that employees will have access to based on the success of the location.

180
00:18:59,926 --> 00:19:04,908
We will encourage employee growth and will promote skills that will be transferable beyond the cannabis industry.

181
00:19:05,368 --> 00:19:07,509
We will touch on this again later in the presentation,

182
00:19:07,888 --> 00:19:17,792
but it is important for us to note that we have signed a labor peace agreement with UFCW Local 1445 to ensure that employee voice is always paramount.

183
00:19:23,754 --> 00:19:29,136
As mentioned previously, we will use a small to midsize fleet of three all electric.

184
00:19:30,436 --> 00:19:33,137
Do I need to let anybody in the room or is someone else able to do that?

185
00:19:33,177 --> 00:19:35,098
I just saw someone jump in the room.

186
00:19:36,957 --> 00:19:40,138
Okay, great, perfect, thank you.

187
00:19:40,258 --> 00:19:45,499
As mentioned previously, we will use a small to mid-sized fleet of three all-electric vehicles.

188
00:19:46,299 --> 00:19:57,401
We are excited to bring an all-electric cannabis delivery fleet to Medford, which means zero exhaust and emissions, and zero engine noises, which ensures we are always respectful to our neighbors.

189
00:19:58,001 --> 00:20:06,363
Each vehicle used to deliver product will be outfitted with the highest standards of security, including a mobile vault system, GPS tracking, and a two-person crew.

190
00:20:06,883 --> 00:20:09,145
The vehicle is never left alone with product inside.

191
00:20:09,685 --> 00:20:14,848
Each vehicle will have an estimated range of up to 250 to 300 miles on a single charge.

192
00:20:15,549 --> 00:20:19,792
A fleet and asset management software platform will ensure efficient usage.

193
00:20:20,952 --> 00:20:26,476
En route, we will offer parking on site for all delivery vehicles and 15 employee parking spaces.

194
00:20:27,117 --> 00:20:30,579
We thought it was important to show you the types of vehicle we will be operating.

195
00:20:30,619 --> 00:20:36,443
So you can see the BrightJob Xevo 400 right there.

196
00:20:41,143 --> 00:20:50,188
As this is a warehouse model, our security protocols will be focused on ensuring only employees have access to the site and that we run an efficient operation with the minimum impact to the surrounding community.

197
00:20:50,609 --> 00:20:58,613
With continued dialogue with surrounding neighbors, neighborhood associations, and the Medford police, we will add state-of-the-art security cameras to ensure the security of the site.

198
00:20:59,194 --> 00:21:04,637
All cameras will be shared live and in real time with Medford police should they wish access.

199
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:09,440
At our Newberry Street adult use facility, all doors are access controlled

200
00:21:09,996 --> 00:21:15,258
We have 65 cameras, 58 interior, seven exterior, and all systems are redundant.

201
00:21:15,698 --> 00:21:25,363
With all the security, it is also important for us to note that our facility does not appear to be a prison or some other type of institutional facility.

202
00:21:25,863 --> 00:21:31,365
We will maintain the existing facade and we'll ensure that our operation blends into the fabric of the neighborhood.

203
00:21:34,787 --> 00:21:39,729
On this slide, you will see a five-year projection of revenues for en route given a certain number of inputs.

204
00:21:40,216 --> 00:21:48,178
We have used the capacity model, which we feel will be more efficient and lead to less vehicles on the roads on a continuous basis.

205
00:21:48,678 --> 00:21:52,159
This slide also shows the projected HCA payments to the city of Medford.

206
00:21:52,579 --> 00:21:56,700
I'm confident there are questions on this slide, so we can absolutely circle back during Q&A.

207
00:21:59,741 --> 00:22:07,643
As we are a business that does not see customers in person or on site, we will create a good neighbor pledge, which will be signed by all employees.

208
00:22:08,178 --> 00:22:14,361
This pledge will ensure that all employees are held accountable and fully respect the community that has invited our operations.

209
00:22:14,841 --> 00:22:21,984
The pledge will state that employees will not smoke cigarettes in public areas, will not loiter, will keep noise to a minimum, and will not park illegally.

210
00:22:22,484 --> 00:22:25,025
We will work with residents and the city to add to this pledge.

211
00:22:25,525 --> 00:22:29,267
Failure to adhere to this pledge will be considered an offense worthy of termination.

212
00:22:30,047 --> 00:22:36,190
In addition to the zero to 3% discretionary impact tax, which will be directed to the city of Medford as defined in our HCA,

213
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:39,370
We plan to work with the city of Medford to fund a grant program.

214
00:22:39,791 --> 00:22:49,372
This program will be administered by a board of residents, business owners, and nonprofit leaders from the Medford community who will determine what worthy causes will receive the funds.

215
00:22:50,072 --> 00:22:53,993
Our profit sharing program is unique to En Route and our sister company Rooted In.

216
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:57,414
We will profit share with our employees based on company success.

217
00:22:58,014 --> 00:23:05,175
As you can see, employees are important to us and ensuring they can afford to live, work, play, and own in our communities is very important.

218
00:23:05,654 --> 00:23:10,075
We've created an employee home buyer program, which you can see detailed on the screen.

219
00:23:11,516 --> 00:23:17,838
There will be an effort to monitor health impacts on the neighborhood.

220
00:23:18,058 --> 00:23:22,860
And as parents ourselves, we will monitor any impact our presence may have on the local youth population.

221
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:27,861
We'll work with the Medford Health Department on ways to combat the burden of hard drugs and opiate abuse.

222
00:23:28,482 --> 00:23:32,683
In consultation with the Medford Health Department, the mayor's office, and local healthcare leaders,

223
00:23:33,110 --> 00:23:39,335
will develop a fund which will be directed to increase positive outcomes to those working to recover from substance abuse disorder.

224
00:23:43,978 --> 00:23:44,839
Diversity planning.

225
00:23:45,639 --> 00:23:51,684
En Route Medford is 100% person of color owned and 50% of its structure is social equity.

226
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:54,846
We've created a very unique investor model.

227
00:23:56,027 --> 00:24:01,551
It was first established at our Newberry Street location, which saw 55 of our

228
00:24:03,048 --> 00:24:09,653
excuse me, 53 of our 55 investors being people of color and 47% of our investors being women.

229
00:24:10,414 --> 00:24:14,297
We wanted to ensure that our investor model was approachable to all.

230
00:24:14,757 --> 00:24:16,618
So it's not a $50,000 investment.

231
00:24:16,658 --> 00:24:20,802
It actually starts at $1,200 with as much as $100,000.

232
00:24:21,822 --> 00:24:30,489
This model allows us to not only benefit ourselves and our employees through the operation of this business, but also it allows us to create generational wealth.

233
00:24:31,445 --> 00:24:34,149
specifically generational wealth in communities of color.

234
00:24:35,951 --> 00:24:50,608
Additionally, you can see the hiring construction as well as how we plan to work with growers with a preference to BIPOC and veteran growers in Massachusetts.

235
00:24:57,710 --> 00:25:07,336
We've engaged in meaningful conversations with abutters, neighbors, businesses, community leaders, as well as Medford-based stakeholders, and have garnered nearly 50 letters of support.

236
00:25:08,217 --> 00:25:13,840
As mentioned previously, we've proudly signed a labor peace agreement with UFCW Local 1445.

237
00:25:14,460 --> 00:25:19,103
They are the Massachusetts union that represents cannabis workers statewide.

238
00:25:19,624 --> 00:25:25,107
We've also engaged with a local chapter of a national civil rights organization.

239
00:25:31,376 --> 00:25:33,737
And here you can see our difference.

240
00:25:34,897 --> 00:25:41,999
Starting with our mission as our guide, our greatest differentiator is our investment team and our approach to building generational wealth for communities of color.

241
00:25:42,379 --> 00:25:46,720
We want to bring cannabis businesses to our community that are owned and operated by residents of color.

242
00:25:47,601 --> 00:25:55,843
We have deployed a unique investment model, which works to give disenfranchised communities a seat at the table at the ground floor of this burgeoning industry.

243
00:25:56,590 --> 00:26:04,053
As far as hiring, we'll hire members of the local community with a focus on those with past candidates and fractions.

244
00:26:04,073 --> 00:26:09,976
5% of location equity will be set aside for employees and a profit share, which we have gone into.

245
00:26:10,776 --> 00:26:17,499
We pledge to be good neighbors, give back through grants and monitor and remedy any adverse health impacts.

246
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:23,702
With that, I'd like to thank you for your time, and I look forward to your questions.

247
00:26:32,612 --> 00:26:37,454
Thank you, Brian and the en route team for that.

248
00:26:44,756 --> 00:26:51,859
And as mentioned, happy to bring up anything that requires additional detail or anything that needs to be zoomed in.

249
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:54,860
OK, I'll start again.

250
00:26:55,860 --> 00:26:59,262
Assuming that you were to be given the green light to

251
00:27:01,258 --> 00:27:03,319
work from Medford, how soon could be up and running?

252
00:27:04,659 --> 00:27:09,982
Our goal is to be operational by winter of 2023.

253
00:27:10,922 --> 00:27:20,766
We've gained a lot of experience learning the state's process and just understanding the construction process.

254
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:30,610
It is a relatively unique construction process, not unique to construction, but there are certain things that cannabis requires as far as security and protocols and things of that nature.

255
00:27:31,318 --> 00:27:42,263
So we've gained a lot of that experience on Newberry Street, we started Newberry Street in January of 2021, and we expect to be open, either late November, early December.

256
00:27:43,124 --> 00:27:51,468
So we think that, you know, given our experience knowledge, we can do better than that two year mark with this facility.

257
00:27:58,624 --> 00:27:59,404
Thank you, Brian.

258
00:27:59,685 --> 00:28:10,870
Can you talk to me a little bit more about your employee training and the system you're going to use for age verification, both, you know, the initial sale and delivery?

259
00:28:12,090 --> 00:28:12,311
Sure.

260
00:28:12,811 --> 00:28:19,254
So with regards to age verification, the customers will initially upload

261
00:28:20,273 --> 00:28:25,315
their IDs onto a portal online when they are initially placing their order.

262
00:28:25,775 --> 00:28:43,163
That way we're checking IDs, obviously it's not an official check, but we're checking IDs, giving it a tertiary scan to ensure that the individual is 21, to ensure that the address that we're delivering to is an address that we can legally deliver to because there are restrictions on delivery.

263
00:28:43,823 --> 00:28:48,705
Once our drivers are on site, they will have

264
00:28:49,767 --> 00:29:01,294
ID scanners that offer passport quality checks of those IDs to ensure that they are the individuals who they say they are and that it is a valid ID.

265
00:29:02,275 --> 00:29:10,880
For if this is what we do in our dispensary, it also probably happen less.

266
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:18,284
But if there is someone with an out of state, excuse me, foreign ID, we would ask for a second form of identification as well.

267
00:29:18,662 --> 00:29:22,544
That'll probably happen less because we will see a lot of tourists in person.

268
00:29:22,964 --> 00:29:27,446
But for delivery, it's typically going to be the individual that resides at that residence.

269
00:29:27,486 --> 00:29:37,891
But if there is someone from out of state that's visiting, you know, we wouldn't, as long as they can provide a second form of identification, we would allow them to make that purchase.

270
00:29:38,952 --> 00:29:47,776
And then as far as training, all employees must go through a minimum of eight hours of standardized training from the state.

271
00:29:48,970 --> 00:29:59,776
And then we will provide our own internal training as far as customer service, you know, securing themselves, securing the product and things of that nature.

272
00:30:02,277 --> 00:30:05,199
Training is actually very important to us at our Newberry Street site.

273
00:30:05,579 --> 00:30:11,222
We actually set aside about 300 square feet specifically for training space.

274
00:30:11,962 --> 00:30:16,385
We don't have a big facility, but we wanted to make sure that we had the ability to

275
00:30:17,242 --> 00:30:34,596
train our employees, and we anticipate doing something very similar in Medford to ensure that, you know, when we are ready to put someone on the road or even individuals who are working in our warehouse, there's a standard level of service and a standard level of training that everyone has.

276
00:30:37,904 --> 00:30:39,144
Thanks.

277
00:30:39,924 --> 00:30:42,625
Could you speak to the surrounding communities?

278
00:30:42,665 --> 00:30:47,006
Like, what's the area that you're planning on having deliveries to?

279
00:30:47,066 --> 00:30:49,026
Like, what's your expansion?

280
00:30:50,247 --> 00:30:50,527
Sure.

281
00:30:50,627 --> 00:31:07,130
So the way the rules work at the state level is that as a delivery operator, we're only allowed to deliver to communities who have approved cannabis in their municipality.

282
00:31:07,747 --> 00:31:15,571
Um, so for us, we expect to start small and start with, um, a catchment area that is Medford only.

283
00:31:15,591 --> 00:31:30,098
Um, then we anticipate, you know, as we grow, um, and as we bring on additional vehicles and additional personnel, um, that we would grow into the communities that surround Medford who have, um, allowed for cannabis delivery.

284
00:31:30,118 --> 00:31:34,960
Um, there's only so far that you can go, um, because, you know, there's only

285
00:31:35,437 --> 00:31:41,781
so much product that you can have in the vehicle at a time, plus there's a point where it becomes inefficient to go out so far.

286
00:31:42,322 --> 00:31:51,848
So I would say we would probably go one or two communities beyond Medford, and then we would revisit to determine if it makes sense to go further than that.

287
00:32:00,138 --> 00:32:10,147
And will your vehicles be have signage on them or are they just going to be like I saw the vehicles you showed said the onboard or whatever would you have vehicles be identifiable are they just going to be.

288
00:32:12,489 --> 00:32:24,299
No, so the rules state that all vehicles have to be completely nondescript the the pictures that you saw were promotional pictures for that vehicle so it actually said the.

289
00:32:24,803 --> 00:32:26,925
name of the company that manufactures it.

290
00:32:27,045 --> 00:32:36,315
Our vehicles would be completely nondescript, likely white or black vehicles, something that just looks like any other delivery vehicle on the street.

291
00:32:36,895 --> 00:32:37,136
Great.

292
00:32:37,796 --> 00:32:39,258
Okay, appreciate that.

293
00:32:43,443 --> 00:32:44,964
