307
00:34:09,636 --> 00:34:12,157
No, the industry is very new.

308
00:34:12,788 --> 00:34:18,090
Um, we don't, uh, we don't have specific, um, marijuana experience.

309
00:34:18,470 --> 00:34:31,514
Most locals, um, you know, true locals, um, to Massachusetts won't have marijuana experience because marijuana has only been legal on the recreational side for about four years and about six or seven years on the medical side.

310
00:34:32,074 --> 00:34:34,935
So, you know, my background is not cannabis.

311
00:34:34,955 --> 00:34:36,435
My background is private aviation.

312
00:34:37,636 --> 00:34:38,756
Um, that being said.

313
00:34:39,718 --> 00:34:45,260
Salman and Rokia do come with a background of regulated industries.

314
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:50,002
They, you know, are former owners of lounges.

315
00:34:50,902 --> 00:34:53,803
So they, you know, and they also own the restaurant.

316
00:34:53,843 --> 00:34:56,024
So they, you know, deal with alcohol.

317
00:34:56,084 --> 00:35:00,666
And I think alcohol is the closest thing right now to cannabis.

318
00:35:00,706 --> 00:35:03,607
So as it pertains to experience, we don't have

319
00:35:04,083 --> 00:35:09,727
direct experience, but I think as a group, we do have parallel experience to the industry.

320
00:35:10,608 --> 00:35:23,176
The way the regs were written was very similar to how the alcohol and liquor regulations are written, obviously with more specifics towards the plant and cannabis and things like that.

321
00:35:24,497 --> 00:35:26,099
And it's a lot, it is more strict.

322
00:35:26,999 --> 00:35:33,664
The cannabis regs are more strict than alcohol, but we do have, I would call it parallel experience.

323
00:35:35,515 --> 00:35:36,415
I thank you for the answer.

324
00:35:36,455 --> 00:35:37,816
And again, I don't, I don't mean to apply that.

325
00:35:37,856 --> 00:35:38,716
I think it's a negative.

326
00:35:38,756 --> 00:35:42,258
