337
00:36:38,463 --> 00:36:43,926
I am the political director for United Food and Commercial Workers, Local 1445.

338
00:36:44,687 --> 00:36:53,712
Local 1445 represents approximately 12,000 essential workers throughout the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

339
00:36:54,872 --> 00:37:05,258
You probably know us by the friendly faces of workers at Stop and Shop, Macy's, and more recently at Cannabis Dispensaries.

340
00:37:06,253 --> 00:37:15,081
UFCW nationally represents tens of thousands of cannabis workers throughout the nation from seed to sale.

341
00:37:15,782 --> 00:37:29,275
Here in Massachusetts, local 1445 represents a thousand of cannabis workers in agriculture, production, processing, packaging, delivery, and in medical and adult recreational dispensaries.

342
00:37:30,132 --> 00:37:35,035
Our union is in strong support for Enroute Home Delivery Service.

343
00:37:35,496 --> 00:37:49,305
In addition to being an equity applicant, Enroute has committed to hiring affected residents by the War on Drugs, and that usually means people of color.

344
00:37:50,346 --> 00:37:57,611
Enroute and UFCW Local 1445 has entered into a partnership with a labor peace agreement

345
00:37:58,448 --> 00:37:59,968
otherwise known as an LPA.

346
00:38:00,549 --> 00:38:16,193
Simply put, an LPA is an agreement between a union and an employer where the company agrees to remain neutral during an organizing drive and the union agrees not to engage in any job actions.

347
00:38:16,933 --> 00:38:24,015
In this way, employees will decide to unionize or not without undue influence.

348
00:38:24,255 --> 00:38:24,815
Additionally,

349
00:38:25,475 --> 00:38:36,123
Our union, and this is very important for us, strongly believes that racial equity must have an economic stability as its backbone.

350
00:38:37,108 --> 00:38:52,898
Although the cannabis industry in the state has surpassed $3 billion in gross revenues last year, the Attorney General's office has fined cannabis companies hundreds of thousands of dollars for violations of state labor laws.

351
00:38:53,338 --> 00:38:56,240
This would never happen with a union contract.

352
00:38:56,897 --> 00:39:15,337
Indeed, our collective bargaining agreements, not only contain better wages and benefits in the canvas industry, but also equally as important in non economic matters such as non discrimination clauses upward mobility that respect seniority and shop floor.

353
00:39:15,817 --> 00:39:17,279
union representation.

354
00:39:17,839 --> 00:39:31,791
We also know that en route is equally committed to racial justice in the cannabis industry, and indeed, in all aspects of social and economic justice.

355
00:39:32,451 --> 00:39:44,864
UFCW Local 1445 strongly urges the Cannabis Advisory Committee of Medford to support En Route for their delivery license in Medford.

356
00:39:45,364 --> 00:39:46,105
